The paper presents a novel algorithm for optimizing variational approximations over the space of model parameters and tractable families used for the variational approximation. This is a problem commonly encountered in machine learning and artificial intelligence, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The paper also uses graph partitioning algorithms, which are commonly used in computer science and data science, suggesting that it could also belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also explores the relationship between the graph cut and the GMF approximation, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with optimization, which is a fundamental problem in computer science, suggesting that it could also belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category.
